title: Great products/questionable billing
text:
There‚Äôs no arguing that Temu has some great products at good, affordable prices. The designs featured in a lot of departments are funkier than they a year or so ago, more modern and keeping with current design trends. There‚Äôs something here for everyone though regardless of your tastes. On the whole I‚Äôve been very pleased with the quality of the products I have purchased. Great prices and well made clothing, etc. I expect the pieces I purchased to last, just be careful of any garments with a large percentage of polyester - they will pill after machine washing. I tried to stick with 100 percent cotton.

That said, despite their apparently meticulous receipts and records, it still results in some confusion and I was distressed to find some discrepancies between what they say I was charged for and what I actually paid. I have not broached this with Customer Service yet so I cannot comment on how they will handle this. However, I have had other issues like a lost package & they were very accommodating and helpful, giving me credit for one portion of the total order even though the box was eventually located.

The prices change rapidly so stay on top of that & get refunds for any price drops. Often there are multiple listings for items that will show them for different price points, do your due diligence! Some descriptions of items were not accurate(a bedspread that is definitely not a ‚Äòquilt‚Äô), but on the whole I have been very pleased with the quality of the items I have purchased. The workmanship is not shoddy & I expect the items to last. And you can‚Äôt beat the prices! The designs are funky and fun. I always want more than I can afford!
